<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kolina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, unless you are very familiar with the Cleric Epic, you need not read this, but if you are....here goes.<P>Ok, my best friend is a lvl 58 cleric.  We completed every step of the cleric epic up until the Zordak Ragefire.   We killed Ragefire, and when the dragon spawned, we threw everything at him we had....and failed  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif">.   We had him down to the Z in his name when the last tank died, and the castors just kept getting summoned and killed (some died as many as 10 times in the attempt.)<P>Here's my question....is there ANYthing we can do to short circuit the quest without having to start over at step one.   We still have the Orb of Frozen Water and the Orb of Clear Water, and simply need that last orb, but every step of the cleric epic seems to depend on the step before it.   All we actually need is the Message to Natasha to turn into Natasha to get the Shimmering Pearl which will cause the dragon to spawn.  We need Lord Gimblox Signet Ring (which we have) to turn in to get the 2nd Ornate Sea Shell to turn in to get the message.  Now my question is, has anyone ever encountered this before?  Natasha Whitewater is involved in the quest in 3 different places.   Is it possible to turn in something meant for the 3rd Natasha to the first Natasha that resides in Lake Rathe, or does it have to be the proper Natasha spawned in the proper way?  I'm assuming that it does, but am not sure.   We tried to piggyback with another cleric last night and it didn't work.  He had the plasmatic priest robe to turn in, which spawned the Natasha that we needed.   We were hoping beyond hope that once he spawned and used that Natasha, she would stay around long enough for my friend to also turn in her ring, but Natasha poofed as soon as the first cleric turned in his ring and got his sea shell II.<P>ANY ideas would be extremely helpful.   Can you imagine having to do your entire epic twice?!   We are ready to start over, but this is my last ditch effort to see if anyone else has encountered this and found a way around it.<P>Thanks</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Walterscott</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I messed up my epic on my first attempt after killing the plasmatic priest.  So I needed to start all the way over.  I'm currently one of 25+ clerics on emarr with a pearl, awaiting my shot at Zordak.    <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>Problem with the Natasha spawns is that she is spawned usually after, you turn in an item to the first NPC.  Then she will spawn, and you turn in the 2nd item to her.  Depending on the orbs your friend has, there is a chance that some steps may be able to be side stepped, but it's unlikely. Due to the way each step is interwoven.  <P>I'd guess you should probably go thru each step and determine based upon the globes you have and what he's missing to spawn Zordak again.<P>Sorry, but it may not be that good of news.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cayleu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I hate to say it, but I think you have to start over : ( You absolutely must kill off Zordak, if your not sure you have enough people to overkill him yet, do not fight him and give him up for another day if you have to.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">MegonBefallenbane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm, same thing happened to a friend of mine.  Think he ended up doing the entire quest again, though.<P>I would think that if you have Gimblox's ring, then you should be able to just turn that in to the second Natasha to get the correct shell to give to Naxot.  Now, the only problem you'll run into is whether or not Natasha poofs right when the person at that stage of the quest hands her the ring.  I'd say try piggybacking again to see if you can give the ring to Natasha.  If she poofs again, then it seems like you'll have to start the quest completely over.  Something you may want to try too...if both clerics have the trade window open with Natasha, that could keep her from poofing when the first cleric hits the trade button, since another transaction is already in progress.  Then the second one might be able to do it.  Just a thought though, not sure how that would work.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=8029" TARGET=_blank>Megon Befallenbane</A><BR><UL TYPE=SQUARE><BR><LI>Gnomish Vicar of 53 blessings<BR><LI><A HREF="http://www.mtncom.com/hawkwoods/" TARGET=_blank>Hawkwood's Legion</A><BR><LI>Rodcet Nife<BR></UL></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zakalwe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When I turned in my note to Natasha to receive the shimmering pearl, she didn't immediately despawn. I hung around for a couple of minutes just doing stuff, and she was still up, so if you get another cleric at that stage you might want to tag along and see if she stays up after they hand in their stuff. Good luck!<P>I got my pearl about 5 weeks ago, and have not got Ragefire yet - what with other clerics also needing him, and the recent server outages, I've all but given up hope.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Zakalwe Soulwarden<BR>Plum Templar of Rivervale<BR>Grey Council, Xev</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AilenGoldenfire_Quellious</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I did my Ragefire BEFORE doing Overking, and can confirm that this works.<P>Camp Berg, kill Priest, camp Gimblox, go spawn Ixiblat Fer, but you do'nt have to kill him. <BR>You will get the message to natasha from Naxot, and then just accompany a cleric who has his sceptre/note to Omat, and when he turns in his stuff and gets his pearl (Message to Natasha) you can turn in yours afterwards.<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
